	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65215041">Honestly, that would be my pick too.  Wolfenstein _introduced_ the raycasting technology that made 3D first-person shooters possible, but Doom _popularized_ it, and game studios have been churning out at least two 3D first-person games for every one anything-else, ever since.<br><br>Personally, I don't like the genre; but it's impossible to deny that it has been influential.</div>
