	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65215057"><p>Super Mario 64 was the first third person 3D game with controls and a camera that actually worked well. It was also the first game to play well with an analog control stick. There were earlier first person 3D games on the Playstation, but the controls were terrible and camera behavior could obscure the player, which made most of those games awful. Mario 64 taught game developers how 3D should work and it changed first person 3D games from technology demos to fun games. It also prepared developers for Sony<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

