	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65215321"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elite_(video_game)" title="wikipedia.org">ELITE<span class="substr"> </span></a> [wikipedia.org] in 1984 was one of the first open-world games (8 procedural generated galaxies with 255 planets and a "witchspace" full of nasty aliens), 3D games (originally wire frame with hidden line removal, some later version had solid planes), allowing to play as a trader or as a pirate or as a bounty hunter or as a miner (or a combination of those), requiring the players to upgrade the equipment of their ship, and some missions to do - all in 22 kilobytes.
<br> <br>
It was also the first game to come with a <a href="http://www.iancgbell.clara.net/elite/dkwheel.htm" title="clara.net">novella</a> [clara.net], b</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65215321">

